SIMPLE: freestone
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Freestone
<hw>Free"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A stone composed
of sand or grit; -- so called because it is easily cut or
wrought.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freestone</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Freestone
<hw>Free"stone`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the flesh readily
separating from the stone, as in certain kinds of peaches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Free-swimming</ent>⟦br⟧
